text: Is there a truth about my current life path that I might be resisting?
When did I last experience a profound sense of authenticity and aliveness?
Deep down, what am I genuinely yearning for at this moment?
Which activities make me completely lose track of time?
Are there core values I feel I'm currently neglecting in my daily life?
If fear were not a factor, what action would I take right now?
Imagine my younger, more idealistic self; what advice would they offer me today?
Can I identify one small, manageable step towards clarity I can take today?
Whose definition of success am I unconsciously trying to live up to?
Even amidst this confusion, for what am I truly grateful?
Which areas of my life feel most out of alignment with my authentic self?
Are there any passions I've set aside that I could revisit for joy or inspiration?
Identify environments or people that drain my energy versus those that energize me.
Am I seeking external permission for something I already know I need to do?
What is my intuition quietly whispering to me about my situation?
If I had to describe my current state in one honest sentence, what would it be?
Recall past challenges I've overcome; how can they offer strength now?
Regardless of scale, what kind of impact do I truly wish to make?
What am I currently tolerating that I know, deep down, I shouldn't be?
Describe the feeling of 'coming home to myself'; what does that entail for me?
